main event: A witness in Kettering, Ohio observed an object with dim green, bright white, and red/green flashing lights, which was later concluded to be a probable aircraft.
interesting points: The witness observed the object for 6 minutes while driving.
The object was described as having dim green on the left side, bright white light on the right side, and red/green flashing lights.
The questionnaire contained detailed information about the observation, including time, duration, and the observer's location.
The witness was asked to provide information about the condition of the sky, the position of the sun, moon, and stars, and the size and movement of the object.
The observer's education and job (motor engine) were part of the information requested in the questionnaire.
sighted object: unidentified object with dim green, bright white, and red/green flashing lights
